C=====True=====71
One anti-Vietnam War politician with this surname inspired young voters to cut their hair to
show support for his campaign. That man with this surname won the 1968 New Hampshire
primary but lost the Democratic nomination. Joseph Welch asked “Have you no sense of
decency, sir?” to a politician with this surname, who claimed to have a list of 205 suspect
individuals. For the point, name this shared surname of Minnesota Congressman Eugene and
anti-Communist Wisconsin Senator Joseph.=====
McCarthy =====